parameters.name: externalEUtranCellFDDId  externalEUtranCellTDDId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[  ]-[  ]  Example:   If MCC=125, MNC=46 , eNBId=10243 , and                   localCellId=30, then                   externalEUtranCellFDDId will be                   12546-10243-30.  Exists for MO classes:  ExternalEUtranCellFDD.ExternalEUtranCellFDDId     ExternalEUtranCellTDD.ExternalEUtranCellTDDId

parameters.name: eUtranCellRelationId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[  ]-[  ], where localCellId applies to the                 case where the cell is in another RBS. If both cells are in the same RBS,                   cellId applies. That is, the                   eUtranCellRelationId corresponds to CGI, which refers to the                 target cell. ,                     Example:   If the target cell has MCC=125, MNC=46eNBId=10243 , and localCellId=30 ,, then                   eUtranCellRelationId will be                   12546-10243-30.

parameters.name: externalUtranCellFDDId  externalUtranCellTDDId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[ RNC-ID ]-[  ]  Example:   If MCC=125, MNC=46 , and rncId=1024 and                   cId=30, then externalUtranCellFDDId will                 be 12546-1024-30.  Bits 1–6 of cellIdentity is cId and bits                 17–28 of cellIdentity is rncId.  Exists for MO classes:  ExternalUtranCellFDD.externalUtranCellFDDId     ExternalUtranCellTDD.externalUtranCellTDDId

parameters.name: utranCellRelationId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[ RNC-ID ]-[  ]  Example:   If the target cell has MCC=125, MNC=46 ,                   rncId=1024 and cId=30 , then                   utranCellRelationId will be                 12546-1024-30.  Bits 1–6 of cellIdentity is cId and bits                 17–28 of cellIdentity is rncId.

parameters.name: externalGeranCellId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[  ]-[  ]  Example:   If MCC=125, MNC=46 , lac=10243 , and                   cellIdentity=30 , then externalGeranCellId                 will be 12546-10243-30.

parameters.name: geranCellRelationId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[  ]-[  ]  Example:   If the target cell has MCC=125, MNC=46                   ,lac=10243 , and cellIdentity=30 , then                   geranCellRelationId will be                 12546-10243-30.

parameters.name: externalGUtranCellId
parameters.type: The Automated Neighbor Relations feature constructs the RDN of the MO as                 follows:  [  ][  ]-[ leading 0s ( length : 32- gNodeBIdLength ) ][ < gNBId > ]-[  ]  Example:   If MCC=123, MNC=45, Node_MCC=125, Node_MNC=46 ,                   gNBId=10243 , gNodeBIdLength=22 , and                   localCellId=30 , then externalGUtranCellId                 will be 12546-000000000010243-30. The Node_MCC&Node_MNC is used for RDN

parameters.name: externalGNodeBFunctionId
